		<title>U.S. to ban some airline passengers from carrying larger electronics</title>


		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - Passengers traveling on certain U.S.-bound foreign airline flights will have to check electronic devices larger than a cell phone once U.S. authorities formalize a new ban in response to an unspecified terrorism threat, U.S. officials told Reuters on Monday.&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
