		<title>Trump's Russian imbroglio prompts Republican rethink on surveillance law</title>


		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - Some Republican lawmakers appear to be reassessing whether to make changes to a surveillance law that allows broad snooping of Internet communications, citing concerns over the handling of classified intercepts after leaks of conversations between Russian officials and American associates of President Donald Trump.&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
