		<title>Exclusive: Tillerson plans to skip NATO meeting, visit Russia in April - sources</title>


		<description>WASHINGTON (Reuters) - U.S. Secretary of State Rex Tillerson plans to skip an April 5-6 meeting of NATO foreign ministers for a U.S. visit by the Chinese president and will travel to Russia later in the month, U.S. officials said on Monday, a step allies may see as putting Moscow's concerns ahead of theirs.&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
